1
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:15,767
Eden!

2
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:16,733
My mom!

3
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:18,467
Who is Yenyen, Sabina?

4
00:00:18,533 --> 00:00:21,167
She was with us on the island.

5
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:23,000
Help!

6
00:00:23,067 --> 00:00:26,033
Yenyen!

7
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,300
Mom!

8
00:00:27,367 --> 00:00:29,167
I hope Yenyen is fine.

9
00:00:29,233 --> 00:00:31,533
I'll feel bad for her parents
if she doesn't make it back.

10
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:32,533
Mom!

11
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:35,467
- Eden!
- Mom!

12
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:38,067
I hope she is reunited
with her family.

13
00:00:38,133 --> 00:00:40,633
She gave me courage.

14
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:42,800
I hope she's been saved, too.

15
00:00:42,867 --> 00:00:46,267
He gave me this bracelet.

16
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:49,267
He took care of me
when we were on the island.

17
00:00:49,333 --> 00:00:51,367
She's a good kid.

18
00:00:51,433 --> 00:00:53,800
She's from a good family.

19
00:00:53,867 --> 00:00:56,533
His parents raised him well.

20
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,533
I want to meet her.

21
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:02,567
I want to thank him personally
for helping you.

22
00:01:02,633 --> 00:01:05,467
I will introduce her to you
when I see her again.

23
00:01:05,533 --> 00:01:08,133
I'm sure you'll like him, Mom.

24
00:01:08,233 --> 00:01:09,367
If we'll see each other,

25
00:01:09,433 --> 00:01:12,500
He'll be a part of our family.

26
00:01:12,567 --> 00:01:17,233
I will treat her as my own.

27
00:01:18,467 --> 00:01:21,100
I thank God that
you're here with me.

28
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:23,433
And we're not wasting any time.

29
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:26,033
I will care for you
and do everything

30
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:28,467
to give you a better future.

31
00:01:28,533 --> 00:01:31,000
Red and I are here, Hon.

32
00:01:31,067 --> 00:01:33,233
Yes. Let's just meet
at the restaurant.

33
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:34,267
All right.

34
00:01:35,333 --> 00:01:36,500
That was your dad.

35
00:01:36,567 --> 00:01:38,267
We'll just meet him
at the restaurant.

36
00:01:38,333 --> 00:01:39,300
Okay.

37
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:49,333
Mom, I will buy a phone.

38
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:53,233
I want to call the airline
about Yenyen's whereabouts.

39
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:54,300
I'll go with you.

40
00:01:54,367 --> 00:01:56,100
No, it's okay. I got it.

41
00:01:56,167 --> 00:01:57,433
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

42
00:01:57,500 --> 00:01:58,533
Okay.

43
00:01:58,600 --> 00:01:59,667
I'll just see you
at the restaurant.

44
00:01:59,733 --> 00:02:00,533
- I'll see you.
- All right, see you!

45
00:02:02,033 --> 00:02:03,467
I'm just going to buy something,
Mom. My treat.

46
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,533
Zandro.

47
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,367
What?

48
00:02:26,533 --> 00:02:29,433
You should know what to do.

49
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:33,267
Take it out on his relatives.

50
00:02:33,333 --> 00:02:35,500
Just pick one.

51
00:02:35,567 --> 00:02:38,433
You'll see how fast
it will work.

52
00:02:39,467 --> 00:02:40,500
My gosh.

53
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,100
Oh, wow!

54
00:02:49,233 --> 00:02:50,533
What a small world.

55
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:52,600
Do I really have
to see you here?

56
00:02:52,667 --> 00:02:55,033
Why? Can you afford this place?

57
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:58,300
I'm sure you only have enough
money for transportation.

58
00:02:58,367 --> 00:03:01,733
Money for transportation
and good character.

59
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:06,067
While you have to ride a big car
to carry your horn and tail.

60
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:50,033
Yenyen.

61
00:03:52,233 --> 00:03:53,600
Sorry, I thought
you were my friend.

62
00:04:05,133 --> 00:04:06,567
You always have a lot to say.

63
00:04:06,633 --> 00:04:08,600
- Come on, Eden.
- Oh, my goodness.

64
00:04:08,667 --> 00:04:10,500
This must be your daughter.

65
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:14,300
Eden, right?

66
00:04:14,367 --> 00:04:16,067
She's still alive.

67
00:04:16,133 --> 00:04:17,467
It's too bad.

68
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:21,533
I ordered a coffin
that's a buy one, take one.

69
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,600
Don't worry.

70
00:04:22,667 --> 00:04:25,667
I can still use it soon.

71
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:27,467
- Here! Take this!
- Mom!

72
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:29,133
That's my contribution
in advance,

73
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:31,367
just in case we don't see
each other again.

74
00:04:31,433 --> 00:04:34,000
- You wench! Come here!
- Mom!

75
00:04:34,067 --> 00:04:35,067
You'll pay for this!

76
00:04:35,133 --> 00:04:37,367
- You're such a horrible person!
- Mom!

77
00:04:37,433 --> 00:04:39,367
That's what you deserve!

78
00:04:39,433 --> 00:04:41,333
- That's what you get!
- Mom...

79
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:44,367
You will die before me!

80
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:45,300
- Mom.
- You're gonna come near me?

81
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:49,433
Get off me!

82
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:51,367
Mom, that's enough!
It's embarrassing!

83
00:04:53,067 --> 00:04:54,700
- You're a monster!
- Ma'am Rina, please, stop.

84
00:04:54,767 --> 00:04:57,300
Amanda! You're really something!

85
00:04:57,367 --> 00:05:00,000
You're acting like a criminal!

86
00:05:00,067 --> 00:05:02,300
You shouldn't be out of jail!

87
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:05,367
Did you know that this woman
is a murderer?

88
00:05:05,433 --> 00:05:07,067
She killed my son!

89
00:05:07,133 --> 00:05:08,533
-Ma'am, don't make a scene here!
-She's a liar.

90
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,333
Don't believe her!

91
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:12,500
- Rina, that's enough.
- Please, stop!

92
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:14,333
- She killed my son.
- That's enough.

93
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:16,600
- Stop it.
- She's my wife.

94
00:05:16,667 --> 00:05:18,400
Talk to your wife!

95
00:05:18,467 --> 00:05:19,400
We're not doing anything to her!

96
00:05:21,433 --> 00:05:22,667
This woman provoked me!

97
00:05:22,733 --> 00:05:24,667
She thinks like a criminal.

98
00:05:24,733 --> 00:05:26,333
That's why she's always thirsty
for a fight!

99
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,067
You don't belong here! Get out!

100
00:05:28,133 --> 00:05:29,067
Get out!

101
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:31,033
Murderer!

102
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:31,667
Get out of here!

103
00:05:31,733 --> 00:05:33,433
Get out!

104
00:05:39,233 --> 00:05:40,367
Put that woman in jail!

105
00:05:40,433 --> 00:05:41,700
She needs to go to jail again!

106
00:05:41,767 --> 00:05:43,233
Stop it.

107
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:44,233
Just leave her be.

108
00:05:56,433 --> 00:05:57,567
I'm all dirty now.

109
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,533
What's going on?

110
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:11,267
Such a pest!

111
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:13,267
She makes my blood boil!

112
00:06:15,067 --> 00:06:18,400
Mom, I've been asking you
what happened.

113
00:06:18,467 --> 00:06:19,600
But you've been ignoring me.

114
00:06:21,033 --> 00:06:24,500
I'm sorry if I've been
ignoring you, Red. Okay?

115
00:06:24,567 --> 00:06:27,067
I was trying to calm
myself down.

116
00:06:28,367 --> 00:06:29,733
Just tell me what happened.

117
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:32,100
How can I understand
why you're so mad?

118
00:06:32,167 --> 00:06:33,567
How can I help you?

119
00:06:36,233 --> 00:06:39,033
I saw the woman who killed
your brother.

120
00:06:40,267 --> 00:06:41,400
They let her out of prison.

121
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:42,567
I can't accept

122
00:06:42,633 --> 00:06:46,467
that the woman who killed
your brother is free now.

123
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:49,067
If it wasn't for her...

124
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:53,100
your brother would still
be here.

125
00:06:53,167 --> 00:06:55,167
He would have been with us
right now.

126
00:07:02,233 --> 00:07:03,133
Don't cry.

127
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:06,467
I understand that you're mad.

128
00:07:07,467 --> 00:07:12,100
I don't know know what
to tell them if I was there.

129
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:17,133
And whoever she is, I hate her.

130
00:07:18,533 --> 00:07:20,067
We will never forgive her.

131
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,367
I don't care if she's mad.

132
00:07:25,433 --> 00:07:26,733
But yelling out in public

133
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:30,200
that my mom is an ex-convict
is wrong.

134
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:36,533
That's what she's been doing
since your mom got out of jail.

135
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,167
Oh my gosh.

136
00:07:38,233 --> 00:07:40,033
I'm sorry, Dear.

137
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:42,367
You're getting dragged into it.

138
00:07:42,433 --> 00:07:45,533
Don't worry. We'll stay away
from her next time.

139
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,533
To keep us out of trouble.

140
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,333
Mom, you don't have
to apologize.

141
00:07:49,433 --> 00:07:51,500
You didn't do anything wrong.

142
00:07:51,567 --> 00:07:56,100
I can stand up to anyone
and say you're innocent.

143
00:07:56,167 --> 00:07:58,233
You don't need to get
in a fight.

144
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,133
Me, too.

145
00:08:02,033 --> 00:08:05,267
I always get in a fight
with Rina, right?

146
00:08:05,333 --> 00:08:09,700
But I realized I don't need
to tell anyone I'm innocent.

147
00:08:09,767 --> 00:08:13,133
Only time can tell and prove

148
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:16,567
that I'm a good person
and mother.

149
00:08:16,633 --> 00:08:17,933
It's similar to a can.

150
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,200
It's loud when it's empty.

151
00:08:40,667 --> 00:08:41,633
See you.

152
00:08:47,767 --> 00:08:49,300
Darling, wait, wait, wait.

153
00:08:49,367 --> 00:08:50,633
Wait!

154
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:54,000
Your dad and I will come
to get you later, okay?

155
00:08:55,233 --> 00:08:57,667
After you meet
with your psychiatrist

156
00:08:57,733 --> 00:08:59,200
regarding your therapy.

157
00:08:59,267 --> 00:09:00,600
Mom, you don't have to fetch me.

158
00:09:00,667 --> 00:09:02,367
I can go home on my own.

159
00:09:02,433 --> 00:09:03,667
I know.

160
00:09:03,733 --> 00:09:09,100
But I want to spend
the most time with my son.

161
00:09:09,167 --> 00:09:10,033
I missed you.

162
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:15,167
- Okay, fine.
- Okay, I'll see you later.

163
00:09:15,233 --> 00:09:16,400
- Bye, Darling.
- Bye, Mom.

164
00:09:16,467 --> 00:09:17,633
- Bye.
- Bye, Dad.

165
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:18,700
Bye.

166
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:20,267
- Take care, Son.
- Thank you!

167
00:09:39,767 --> 00:09:40,500
Hon...

168
00:09:43,467 --> 00:09:44,400
we're going to be late.

169
00:09:44,467 --> 00:09:45,433
Okay.

170
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:32,233
Yenyen, where are you now?

171
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:33,567
I hope to see you again.

172
00:10:44,133 --> 00:10:44,667
Red.

173
00:10:48,333 --> 00:10:50,567
Red, it's so good to see you.

174
00:10:50,633 --> 00:10:52,000
I'm glad you're better now.

175
00:10:57,400 --> 00:11:00,967
Sab, where are Yenyen
and Raichu?

176
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:02,367
Did you see them?

177
00:11:02,433 --> 00:11:04,300
What happened to them?

178
00:11:04,367 --> 00:11:05,600
I can't remember anything.

179
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:09,000
Did they get rescued?

180
00:11:12,367 --> 00:11:16,633
I still can't believe that Coach
Vinluan is no longer with us.

181
00:11:20,767 --> 00:11:22,433
Things happen for a reason.

182
00:11:24,167 --> 00:11:25,433
God knows best.

183
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:30,300
What's important is that
she had a wonderful life.

184
00:11:31,433 --> 00:11:35,133
And we will never forget
all the time and hard work

185
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:37,033
she dedicated to us.

186
00:11:39,533 --> 00:11:41,200
That's why I want to help

187
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:44,333
with the preparations
for her tribute.

188
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:46,767
I can do anything.

189
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:49,467
Of course, you are welcome,
Eden.

190
00:11:49,533 --> 00:11:53,200
You're one of the students
that are close to Miss Vinluan.

191
00:11:53,267 --> 00:11:56,367
And you were with her
before she passed away.

192
00:12:02,733 --> 00:12:04,367
Sab, tell me.

193
00:12:04,433 --> 00:12:05,600
Did they get rescued?

194
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:10,433
No.

195
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:11,700
Did we leave them on the island?

196
00:12:13,467 --> 00:12:16,067
No, you didn't do anything
wrong.

197
00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:19,067
I left them behind for you.

198
00:12:21,167 --> 00:12:22,233
I'm sorry.

199
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:24,267
You had an accident.

200
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:26,633
And you hurt your head.

201
00:12:26,700 --> 00:12:31,133
I can't leave you like that.

202
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:35,600
And even if I left you there,
I didn't know how to find them

203
00:12:35,667 --> 00:12:37,533
because I didn't know
where they were.

204
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,600
So...

205
00:12:41,733 --> 00:12:43,600
I had to choose between you...

206
00:12:45,067 --> 00:12:46,500
or Yenyen and Raichu.

207
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:49,400
Because if I didn't
choose you...

208
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:54,500
you could have died
from blood loss.

209
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,667
But I wanted to come back
for them.

210
00:13:00,767 --> 00:13:04,533
I just couldn't do it because
I couldn't leave you behind.

211
00:13:06,467 --> 00:13:09,700
But I told the rescuers
to go back for them.

212
00:13:11,367 --> 00:13:12,500
So tell me...

213
00:13:13,567 --> 00:13:16,233
am I the bad guy here?

214
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:17,333
Did I do anything wrong?

215
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:18,533
Is it my fault?

216
00:13:22,767 --> 00:13:23,500
Sorry.

217
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:28,667
Don't worry about them too much.

218
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,133
I know that...

219
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:34,667
that they're safe, too.

220
00:13:36,367 --> 00:13:37,533
You're not sure about that.

221
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,533
Then what am I supposed to do?

222
00:13:44,067 --> 00:13:47,033
You disappoint me.

223
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:50,500
I thought you'd be thanking me
for saving your life.

224
00:13:51,833 --> 00:13:54,600
But all you think about
is Yenyen.

225
00:13:56,133 --> 00:13:57,067
Unbelievable.

226
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:15,033
You mean you still haven't seen
Red up until now?

227
00:14:22,467 --> 00:14:25,500
I don't know what happened
to him and Sabina.

228
00:14:25,567 --> 00:14:26,633
I know!

229
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:28,233
Their boat probably sunk.

230
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:30,733
That's bad karma for leaving us
on that island.

231
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:34,033
Hey, don't say that!

232
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:35,367
Yes, we're mad at them.

233
00:14:35,433 --> 00:14:38,067
But don't say that.

234
00:14:38,133 --> 00:14:39,300
Okay. Okay, fine.

235
00:14:39,367 --> 00:14:40,467
I'm sorry.

236
00:14:40,533 --> 00:14:42,733
I hope they're okay.

237
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:43,733
Come on!

238
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,300
Let's pray for coach.

239
00:15:05,433 --> 00:15:09,167
Coach always used to tell me...

240
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:13,367
good people are like candles.

241
00:15:14,767 --> 00:15:18,100
They burn themselves up
to give light to others...

242
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:24,033
especially Coach Vinluan.

243
00:15:25,067 --> 00:15:27,367
She was like my candle.

244
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:32,300
She guided me through
everything.

245
00:15:32,367 --> 00:15:33,700
Even on the island,

246
00:15:36,467 --> 00:15:41,267
she became the light and hope
for Red and me.

247
00:15:43,133 --> 00:15:47,233
That's why we have to serve as
a light to others, too, Raichu.

248
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:52,567
It will help others see
what they seek.

249
00:17:01,533 --> 00:17:02,300
Red!

250
00:17:06,767 --> 00:17:07,933
Yen!

251
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:12,367
- Yenyen!
- Red!

252
00:17:35,633 --> 00:17:37,667
Thank God I found you!
I was so worried!

253
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:40,200
We're okay.

254
00:17:40,267 --> 00:17:43,000
I'm glad you saw me!

255
00:17:43,067 --> 00:17:44,167
I was about to go home

256
00:17:44,233 --> 00:17:46,433
when I found out there was
a tribute for Coach Vinluan.

257
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:47,633
She helped us a lot.

258
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:51,467
That's why I decided
to come here.

259
00:17:52,733 --> 00:17:56,067
Maybe it's destiny
that I found you here.

260
00:17:56,133 --> 00:17:57,733
I was so worried.

261
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:59,433
I thought I would never see you
again.

262
00:18:01,533 --> 00:18:04,367
Maybe we met here

263
00:18:04,433 --> 00:18:10,633
because Coach Vinluan wanted
to see that we kept our promise.

264
00:18:12,067 --> 00:18:13,967
I know that Coach Vinluan
is happy for us.

265
00:18:14,033 --> 00:18:15,633
Because we're both safe.

266
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:19,633
Coach!

267
00:18:19,700 --> 00:18:20,900
We made it!

268
00:18:23,433 --> 00:18:25,133
Thank you for all your help.

269
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:30,133
Excuse me.

270
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:32,967
You're acting as if
I don't exist!

271
00:18:33,033 --> 00:18:34,567
Coach, we made it!

272
00:18:34,633 --> 00:18:35,833
Really?

273
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:41,400
Hey! You still have to explain
why you and Sabina ditched us!

274
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:50,433
Hello, Red.

275
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:52,967
Oh, really?

276
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:53,967
That's good to hear.

277
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:56,333
Have fun.

278
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:57,667
You guys enjoy yourselves.

279
00:18:59,133 --> 00:19:00,933
So, he saw Yenyen already?

280
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:03,000
Yeah. He saw her at school.

281
00:19:03,067 --> 00:19:04,500
They're together right now.

282
00:19:04,567 --> 00:19:06,633
I'm sure our son is so happy.

283
00:19:08,167 --> 00:19:13,400
I think Yenyen is more than
a friend to him.

284
00:19:13,467 --> 00:19:15,233
What if...

285
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:17,700
he's in love with her?

286
00:19:17,767 --> 00:19:19,033
Hey, you.

287
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:21,967
Don't jump to conclusions.

288
00:19:22,033 --> 00:19:23,067
As for me...

289
00:19:25,367 --> 00:19:27,400
as long as our son is happy...

290
00:19:29,367 --> 00:19:30,433
I'm happy.

291
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:34,300
I've been thinking...

292
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:40,333
since Red's plane crash
accident...

293
00:19:41,467 --> 00:19:43,167
I realized I have been...

294
00:19:44,567 --> 00:19:45,700
unfair to him.

295
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:50,267
Because since Angelo died,

296
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:54,133
all I've been talking about
was Angelo.

297
00:19:56,367 --> 00:19:57,300
This time...

298
00:19:58,367 --> 00:20:00,133
I'll make it up to him.

299
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,733
Whatever my son wants...

300
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,333
whatever makes him happy,
I'll be happy with it too.

301
00:20:11,167 --> 00:20:13,367
You had an accident?

302
00:20:13,433 --> 00:20:15,133
I woke up in the hospital
in Manila.

303
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:18,700
That's all I remember.

304
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:23,433
Sorry, we had to leave you
because it was an emergency.

305
00:20:25,067 --> 00:20:28,367
Sab had to make a decision
to take me to the hospital.

306
00:20:30,667 --> 00:20:34,167
But she told the rescuers
to come back for you.

307
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:35,567
What matters is that
you're okay now.

308
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:39,100
Raichu's right.

309
00:20:39,167 --> 00:20:41,067
She said something
might have happened.

310
00:20:41,133 --> 00:20:42,500
That's why you left.

311
00:20:45,433 --> 00:20:47,367
Sorry...

312
00:20:47,433 --> 00:20:49,400
I thought you left me.

313
00:20:51,367 --> 00:20:54,333
Yen, you know that
I will never do that.

314
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:56,100
We promised each other,
remember?

315
00:20:56,167 --> 00:21:00,167
Yes, we still have dreams
to fulfill.

316
00:21:00,233 --> 00:21:03,300
Am I part of your dreams?

317
00:21:03,367 --> 00:21:05,267
Because you're included in mine.

318
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:06,500
You're always here...

319
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,700
wherever I go.

320
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:27,233
Amanda, have some coffee first.

321
00:21:35,633 --> 00:21:37,500
You've been doing that
for a while now.

322
00:21:37,567 --> 00:21:40,533
You just got back
from selling rice cakes.

323
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:45,400
I've been thinking
about getting another job.

324
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:47,433
To pay off my debt faster.

325
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:50,500
Can you slow down a little?

326
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:52,767
You might get sick
from overworking.

327
00:21:52,833 --> 00:21:55,033
I don't know why I seem
to rush things.

328
00:21:56,733 --> 00:21:57,900
I feel like I'm making up
for the lost time.

329
00:21:57,967 --> 00:22:00,667
Because I've been separated
from my daughter for so long.

330
00:22:00,733 --> 00:22:04,200
I want to give her everything
that can make her happy.

331
00:22:04,267 --> 00:22:07,233
Amanda, I didn't raise her
in a lavish lifestyle.

332
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:10,367
She'll be happy
with simple things.

333
00:22:10,433 --> 00:22:14,200
So she's happy just to be
with you.

334
00:22:14,267 --> 00:22:15,533
I miss her already.

335
00:22:17,567 --> 00:22:19,700
If only I could stay with her
at all times.

336
00:22:20,733 --> 00:22:21,667
But...

337
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:26,100
if I stick with her,

338
00:22:26,167 --> 00:22:30,367
Rina, that horrible wench, might
take her anger out on her.

339
00:22:30,433 --> 00:22:32,600
I agree!

340
00:22:32,667 --> 00:22:35,167
That wench is taking her anger
out on everyone!

341
00:22:35,233 --> 00:22:36,500
Oh, dear.

342
00:22:36,567 --> 00:22:38,533
She better not try
to hurt my daughter!

343
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:41,300
I'm not afraid to go back
to jail

344
00:22:41,367 --> 00:22:44,000
once she tries to harm Eden!

345
00:22:49,167 --> 00:22:50,667
Wait.

346
00:22:50,733 --> 00:22:52,433
- My mom's calling.
- Go on. Answer it.

347
00:22:54,767 --> 00:22:55,733
Mom.

348
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:57,300
Hi, Red.

349
00:22:57,367 --> 00:23:01,000
Yeah, your dad told me
that Yenyen's been rescued.

350
00:23:01,067 --> 00:23:03,033
Yeah. She's with me right now.

351
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:05,733
That is so good!

352
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:08,400
That's perfect.
I'm on my way there.

353
00:23:08,467 --> 00:23:09,633
I want to meet Yenyen.

354
00:23:09,700 --> 00:23:11,400
Okay.

355
00:23:11,467 --> 00:23:13,567
Okay, we'll wait for you here.

356
00:23:13,633 --> 00:23:15,467
- Take care.
- All right, see you.

357
00:23:23,633 --> 00:23:25,233
I have good news.

358
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:26,367
What is it?

359
00:23:26,433 --> 00:23:28,300
My mom's coming here.

360
00:23:28,367 --> 00:23:32,367
And she wants to meet you.

361
00:23:32,433 --> 00:23:35,600
Red, maybe now is not the time.

362
00:23:35,667 --> 00:23:36,400
Why?

363
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:40,700
I'm worried.
She might not like me.

364
00:23:40,767 --> 00:23:43,300
For sure, your mom is so classy.

365
00:23:43,367 --> 00:23:44,767
My family's poor, Red.

366
00:23:44,833 --> 00:23:46,200
It's embarrassing.

367
00:23:46,267 --> 00:23:47,400
Maybe not today.
I'm not ready yet.

368
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:49,333
Just relax, okay?

369
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:51,000
My mom is a nice person.

370
00:23:51,067 --> 00:23:53,333
And she likes whoever I like.

371
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:55,033
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

372
00:24:07,133 --> 00:24:08,267
Do I look okay?

373
00:24:08,333 --> 00:24:08,933
It's okay.

374
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:11,167
But aren't you feeling hot?

375
00:24:11,233 --> 00:24:13,133
You're sweating.

376
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:14,333
You, too. It's hot out here.

377
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:16,033
No, I'm all good.

378
00:24:18,267 --> 00:24:20,633
My mouth feels dry.

379
00:24:20,700 --> 00:24:22,167
I'll just get some water, okay?

380
00:24:22,233 --> 00:24:23,467
I'll go buy some water.

381
00:24:23,533 --> 00:24:24,467
I'll do it. I'll get you
some water.

382
00:24:24,533 --> 00:24:25,567
No, I got it.

383
00:24:25,633 --> 00:24:27,733
Your mom might be here.

384
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:29,733
No one will come to get her.

385
00:24:29,833 --> 00:24:31,067
I'll get the water.
And I want to freshen up.

386
00:24:31,133 --> 00:24:34,233
I'm embarrassed,
and I'm nervous.

387
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:36,100
Come on, don't be nervous.

388
00:24:36,167 --> 00:24:38,333
My mom is a nice person,
I promise you.

389
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:40,367
I believe you.

390
00:24:40,433 --> 00:24:41,667
I'll go inside.

391
00:24:41,733 --> 00:24:42,433
- Okay. You'll be okay?
- I'll be right back.

392
00:24:42,500 --> 00:24:43,500
Don't take too long.

393
00:24:51,733 --> 00:24:53,500
- Red!
- Hi, Mom! Hi, Dad.

394
00:24:55,233 --> 00:24:57,100
Say goodbye to your dad for now.
He's leaving.

395
00:24:57,167 --> 00:24:58,033
Oh, okay.

396
00:24:58,100 --> 00:24:59,167
- Good luck.
- See you later.

397
00:24:59,233 --> 00:25:00,433
Bye, Hon.

398
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:01,967
He has a meeting with a banker.

399
00:25:02,067 --> 00:25:03,400
Ah, okay.

400
00:25:03,467 --> 00:25:05,167
But I'm excited.

401
00:25:05,233 --> 00:25:06,167
Where is she?

402
00:25:06,233 --> 00:25:07,733
Where is Yenyen?

403
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:08,967
She just went to get
some drinks.

404
00:25:09,033 --> 00:25:10,067
She'll be back.

405
00:25:10,133 --> 00:25:10,700
Okay.

406
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:16,000
By the way, how did your meeting
with your psychiatrist go?

407
00:25:16,067 --> 00:25:16,867
It went well.

408
00:25:16,933 --> 00:25:18,533
He said I needed
a few more sessions.

409
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:21,400
- But I have some improvement.
- That's good, that's good.

410
00:25:21,467 --> 00:25:22,733
You know, in time.

411
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:23,600
Yeah.

412
00:25:49,533 --> 00:25:51,233
Now that Red is back...

413
00:25:52,500 --> 00:25:54,300
I'm ready to deal with Amanda.

414
00:25:54,367 --> 00:25:57,733
I want to make her suffer.

415
00:25:57,800 --> 00:26:02,933
I want to get back at her,
whatever it takes.

416
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:05,433
Raichu, have you seen Yenyen?

417
00:26:05,500 --> 00:26:07,567
I'm texting someone.
Can't you see?

418
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,400
Raichu, if you've seen her,

419
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:11,100
can you please tell me
where she is?

420
00:26:11,167 --> 00:26:12,367
I don't know.

421
00:26:12,433 --> 00:26:14,400
I don't believe you.

422
00:26:14,467 --> 00:26:17,200
Why is the world so small?

423
00:26:17,267 --> 00:26:20,733
Of all people, why did his
mother have to be Ma'am Rina?

424
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:23,533
Do you think your mom
won't understand

425
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:25,133
if you tell the truth?

426
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:26,633
Tell her the truth.

427
00:26:26,700 --> 00:26:28,067
What are you going to tell me?

428
00:26:31,567 --> 00:26:34,967
What truth are you talking
about?
